{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MxCF1dn5nyyfqKwR867xm1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server>\n     2→  <logging traceSpecification=\"JPA=all:com.ibm.ws.jpa.*=all\"/>\n     3→\n     4→  <featureManager>\n     5→    <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n     6→\n     7→    <!-- JPA – BOTH are needed for @PersistenceContext -->\n     8→    <feature>persistence-3.1</feature>\n     9→    <feature>persistenceContainer-3.1</feature>\n    10→\n    11→    <!-- Validation is required because you use @Valid etc. -->\n    12→    <feature>beanValidation-3.0</feature>\n    13→\n    14→    <!-- your MP features -->\n    15→    <feature>mpConfig-3.1</feature>\n    16→    <feature>mpHealth-4.0</feature>\n    17→    <feature>mpOpenAPI-3.1</feature>\n    18→    <feature>mpMetrics-5.1</feature>\n    19→    <feature>mpRestClient-3.0</feature>\n    20→    <feature>mpReactiveMessaging-3.0</feature>\n    21→    <feature>mpJwt-2.1</feature>\n    22→  </featureManager>\n    23→\n    24→  <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"9080\" httpsPort=\"9443\"/>\n    25→\n    26→  <basicRegistry id=\"basic\" realm=\"defaultRealm\">\n    27→    <user name=\"admin\" password=\"adminpwd\"/>\n    28→  </basicRegistry>\n    29→\n    30→  <!-- JDBC driver jar lives in /config/lib/global inside the container -->\n    31→  <library id=\"jdbcLib\">\n    32→    <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib/global\" includes=\"*.jar\"/>\n    33→  </library>\n    34→\n    35→  <dataSource id=\"ordersDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/ordersDS\">\n    36→    <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"jdbcLib\"/>\n    37→    <properties\n    38→      databaseName=\"${env.DB_NAME}\"\n    39→      user=\"${env.DB_USER}\"\n    40→      password=\"${env.DB_PASSWORD}\"\n    41→      serverName=\"${env.DB_HOST}\"\n    42→      portNumber=\"${env.DB_PORT}\"/>\n    43→  </dataSource>\n    44→\n    45→  <webApplication id=\"orders-ui\"\n    46→                location=\"${server.config.dir}/apps/orders-service.war\"\n    47→                contextRoot=\"/\"/>\n    48→\n    49→\n    50→</server>\n    51→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012hhUN9drZKcKh2CcNMsDGD","session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"a8ac1063-ed0f-4bd1-ba19-f1e8895e432d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012hhUN9drZKcKh2CcNMsDGD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary of Findings:\n\nThis is a multi-module Maven project for a coffee shop application using Jakarta EE and MicroProfile, deployed on Open Liberty. Key components:\n\n1. Project Structure:\n- Modules: \n  * common (shared domain classes)\n  * orders-service\n  * barista-service\n  * kitchen-service\n\n2. Technologies:\n- Java 21\n- Jakarta EE 10\n- MicroProfile 6.1\n- Open Liberty\n- Kafka for messaging\n- PostgreSQL for database\n- Maven for build management\n\n3. Key Configuration:\n- Uses environment variables for database connection\n- Kafka messaging for inter-service communication\n- MicroProfile features for config, health checks, metrics, etc.\n\n4. Services:\n- Orders Service: Handles order placement and tracking\n- Barista Service: Processes barista-related commands\n- Kitchen Service: Manages kitchen-related operations\n\n5. Deployment:\n- Uses Docker for containerization\n- Maven Liberty plugin for local development\n- Configurable through server.xml and microprofile-config.properties\n\nWould you like me to dive deeper into any specific aspect of this project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"e1fc27c7-01a9-4ff6-877e-c72a6348f56a"}
