{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XqXcMrhjaf59NrYXZKPnUa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→mp.messaging.connector.liberty-kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP}\n     2→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.connector=liberty-kafka\n     3→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\n     4→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.group.id=kitchen-service\n     5→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.key.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n     6→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n     7→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.connector=liberty-kafka\n     8→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n     9→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.key.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    10→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    11→app.name=kitchen-service\n    12→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"2310ab86-8d8f-43aa-a7db-14c553da2a5a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NkbEATvjeUbyzmn3nca9i4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server>\n     2→  <logging traceSpecification=\"JPA=all:com.ibm.ws.jpa.*=all\"/>\n     3→\n     4→  <featureManager>\n     5→    <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n     6→\n     7→    <!-- JPA – BOTH are needed for @PersistenceContext -->\n     8→    <feature>persistence-3.1</feature>\n     9→    <feature>persistenceContainer-3.1</feature>\n    10→\n    11→    <!-- Validation is required because you use @Valid etc. -->\n    12→    <feature>beanValidation-3.0</feature>\n    13→\n    14→    <!-- your MP features -->\n    15→    <feature>mpConfig-3.1</feature>\n    16→    <feature>mpHealth-4.0</feature>\n    17→    <feature>mpOpenAPI-3.1</feature>\n    18→    <feature>mpMetrics-5.1</feature>\n    19→    <feature>mpRestClient-3.0</feature>\n    20→    <feature>mpReactiveMessaging-3.0</feature>\n    21→    <feature>mpJwt-2.1</feature>\n    22→  </featureManager>\n    23→\n    24→  <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"9080\" httpsPort=\"9443\"/>\n    25→\n    26→  <basicRegistry id=\"basic\" realm=\"defaultRealm\">\n    27→    <user name=\"admin\" password=\"adminpwd\"/>\n    28→  </basicRegistry>\n    29→\n    30→  <!-- JDBC driver jar lives in /config/lib/global inside the container -->\n    31→  <library id=\"jdbcLib\">\n    32→    <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib/global\" includes=\"*.jar\"/>\n    33→  </library>\n    34→\n    35→  <dataSource id=\"ordersDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/ordersDS\">\n    36→    <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"jdbcLib\"/>\n    37→    <properties\n    38→      databaseName=\"${env.DB_NAME}\"\n    39→      user=\"${env.DB_USER}\"\n    40→      password=\"${env.DB_PASSWORD}\"\n    41→      serverName=\"${env.DB_HOST}\"\n    42→      portNumber=\"${env.DB_PORT}\"/>\n    43→  </dataSource>\n    44→\n    45→  <webApplication id=\"orders-ui\"\n    46→                location=\"${server.config.dir}/apps/orders-service.war\"\n    47→                contextRoot=\"/\"/>\n    48→\n    49→\n    50→</server>\n    51→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"316e973f-fef4-4991-a4a8-7f120909e4da"}
