{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LgesjuXMR9TTtES8nwe3qY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→-- Aligns with OrderEntity fields/status usage\n     2→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS orders (\n     3→  id        BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n     4→  customer  VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,\n     5→  item      VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,\n     6→  quantity  INTEGER      NOT NULL CHECK (quantity > 0),\n     7→  status    VARCHAR(20)  NOT NULL,\n     8→  created   TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n     9→  updated   TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()\n    10→);\n    11→\n    12→CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_orders_status ON orders(status);\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"1ce39090-b6ff-4b6a-97a7-355c8e69940d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Mj52vKLonxAyoDra6JNMcZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\n     2→networks:\n     3→  coffee-net:\n     4→\n     5→volumes:\n     6→  pgdata:\n     7→  zkdata:\n     8→  kdata:\n     9→\n    10→services:\n    11→  zookeeper:\n    12→    image: confluentinc/cp-zookeeper:7.5.3\n    13→    container_name: zk\n    14→    environment:\n    15→      ZOOKEEPER_CLIENT_PORT: 2181\n    16→      ZOOKEEPER_TICK_TIME: 2000\n    17→    ports:\n    18→      - \"2181:2181\"\n    19→    networks: [coffee-net]\n    20→    volumes:\n    21→      - zkdata:/var/lib/zookeeper/data\n    22→\n    23→  kafka:\n    24→    image: confluentinc/cp-kafka:7.5.3\n    25→    container_name: kafka\n    26→    depends_on:\n    27→      - zookeeper\n    28→    ports:\n    29→      - \"9092:9092\"   # internal clients in compose can use kafka:9092\n    30→      - \"29092:29092\" # host tools (kcat, etc.) can use localhost:29092\n    31→    environment:\n    32→      KAFKA_BROKER_ID: 1\n    33→      KAFKA_ZOOKEEPER_CONNECT: zookeeper:2181\n    34→\n    35→      # 2 listeners: one for containers (kafka:9092), one for host (localhost:29092)\n    36→      KAFKA_LISTENER_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_MAP: PLAINTEXT:PLAINTEXT,PLAINTEXT_HOST:PLAINTEXT\n    37→      KAFKA_LISTENERS: PLAINTEXT://0.0.0.0:9092,PLAINTEXT_HOST://0.0.0.0:29092\n    38→      KAFKA_ADVERTISED_LISTENERS: PLAINTEXT://kafka:9092,PLAINTEXT_HOST://localhost:29092\n    39→\n    40→      KAFKA_AUTO_CREATE_TOPICS_ENABLE: \"true\"\n    41→      KAFKA_OFFSETS_TOPIC_REPLICATION_FACTOR: 1\n    42→      KAFKA_TRANSACTION_STATE_LOG_MIN_ISR: 1\n    43→      KAFKA_TRANSACTION_STATE_LOG_REPLICATION_FACTOR: 1\n    44→    # ✅ Healthcheck: mark healthy only when the broker responds\n    45→    healthcheck:\n    46→      # Either of these works; pick ONE test line and keep it.\n    47→      # test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"kafka-topics --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --list >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1\"]\n    48→      test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"kafka-broker-api-versions --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1\"]\n    49→      interval: 10s\n    50→      timeout: 5s\n    51→      retries: 10\n    52→      start_period: 20s\n    53→\n    54→    networks: [coffee-net]\n    55→    volumes:\n    56→      - kdata:/var/lib/kafka/data\n    57→\n    58→  postgres:\n    59→    image: postgres:16\n    60→    container_name: postgres\n    61→    environment:\n    62→      POSTGRES_USER: cafe\n    63→      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: cafe\n    64→      POSTGRES_DB: coffeeshop\n    65→    ports:\n    66→      - \"5432:5432\"\n    67→    volumes:\n    68→      - pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data\n    69→      - ./db/init.sql:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/01-init.sql:ro\n    70→    networks: [coffee-net]\n    71→    healthcheck:\n    72→      test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"pg_isready -U cafe -d coffeeshop\"]\n    73→      interval: 5s\n    74→      timeout: 3s\n    75→      retries: 20\n    76→\n    77→  orders-service:\n    78→    container_name: orders-service\n    79→    build:\n    80→      context: ../orders-service\n    81→      dockerfile: Dockerfile\n    82→    environment:\n    83→      # Kafka for containers: use kafka:9092\n    84→      KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP: kafka:9092\n    85→      # DB settings used by server.xml\n    86→      DB_HOST: postgres\n    87→      DB_PORT: 5432\n    88→      DB_NAME: coffeeshop\n    89→      DB_USER: cafe\n    90→      DB_PASSWORD: cafe\n    91→    ports:\n    92→      - \"8081:9080\"   # http\n    93→      - \"9441:9443\"   # https (optional)\n    94→    depends_on:\n    95→      kafka:\n    96→        condition: service_healthy\n    97→      postgres:\n    98→        condition: service_healthy\n    99→    networks: [coffee-net]\n   100→\n   101→  barista-service:\n   102→    container_name: barista-service\n   103→    build:\n   104→      context: ../barista-service\n   105→      dockerfile: Dockerfile\n   106→    environment:\n   107→      KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP: kafka:9092\n   108→    ports:\n   109→      - \"8082:9080\"\n   110→      - \"9442:9443\"\n   111→    depends_on:\n   112→      - kafka\n   113→    networks: [coffee-net]\n   114→\n   115→  kitchen-service:\n   116→    container_name: kitchen-service\n   117→    build:\n   118→      context: ../kitchen-service\n   119→      dockerfile: Dockerfile\n   120→    environment:\n   121→      KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP: kafka:9092\n   122→    ports:\n   123→      - \"8083:9080\"\n   124→      - \"9443:9443\"\n   125→    depends_on:\n   126→      - kafka\n   127→    networks: [coffee-net]\n   128→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"89bf6728-3425-4a7c-a56d-25a1a42fd8ed"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FqGvNUcPL6r2XYBjR9JPMy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<webApplication id=\"orders-service\" location=\"orders-service.war\" contextRoot=\"/\"/>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"55abdb97-2c72-453d-b34c-99de0f713020"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Gfa8zqnKuBkn14SgJwTk47","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<web-app xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n     3→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     4→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\n     5→                             https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/web-app_6_0.xsd\"\n     6→         version=\"6.0\">\n     7→  <display-name>orders-service</display-name>\n     8→\n     9→  <welcome-file-list>\n    10→    <welcome-file>coffeeshopTemplate.html</welcome-file>\n    11→    <welcome-file>index.html</welcome-file>\n    12→  </welcome-file-list>\n    13→</web-app>\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"c08dfde7-53ce-4f8f-92b2-cd141093bd0c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AGrPUQhPw6bBkQGw388f7p","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server>\n     2→  <featureManager>\n     3→    <!-- was: <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature> -->\n     4→    <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n     5→    <feature>mpConfig-3.1</feature>\n     6→    <feature>mpHealth-4.0</feature>\n     7→    <feature>mpOpenAPI-3.1</feature>\n     8→    <feature>mpMetrics-5.1</feature>\n     9→    <feature>mpRestClient-3.0</feature>\n    10→    <feature>mpReactiveMessaging-3.0</feature>\n    11→    <feature>mpJwt-2.1</feature>\n    12→  </featureManager>\n    13→\n    14→  <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"9081\" httpsPort=\"9444\"/>\n    15→\n    16→   <!-- Minimal user registry to satisfy security-enabled features in dev -->\n    17→  <basicRegistry id=\"basic\" realm=\"defaultRealm\">\n    18→    <user name=\"admin\" password=\"adminpwd\"/>\n    19→  </basicRegistry>\n    20→\n    21→  <!-- JDBC config -->\n    22→  <library id=\"jdbcLib\">\n    23→    <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib/global/\" includes=\"*.jar\"/>\n    24→  </library>\n    25→\n    26→  <dataSource id=\"ordersDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/ordersDS\">\n    27→    <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"jdbcLib\"/>\n    28→    <properties databaseName=\"${env.DB_NAME}\" user=\"${env.DB_USER}\" password=\"${env.DB_PASS}\" serverName=\"${env.DB_HOST}\" portNumber=\"${env.DB_PORT}\"/>\n    29→  </dataSource>\n    30→\n    31→</server>\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"bd1f9303-a5c2-48dd-958c-82ac421e1ee5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017MBTG4R7jkJ7Up2i1uy9Up","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server>\n     2→  <featureManager>\n     3→    <!-- was: <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature> -->\n     4→    <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n     5→    <feature>mpConfig-3.1</feature>\n     6→    <feature>mpHealth-4.0</feature>\n     7→    <feature>mpOpenAPI-3.1</feature>\n     8→    <feature>mpMetrics-5.1</feature>\n     9→    <feature>mpRestClient-3.0</feature>\n    10→    <feature>mpReactiveMessaging-3.0</feature>\n    11→    <feature>mpJwt-2.1</feature>\n    12→  </featureManager>\n    13→\n    14→  <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"9082\" httpsPort=\"9445\"/>\n    15→\n    16→  <!-- Minimal user registry to satisfy security-enabled features in dev -->\n    17→  <basicRegistry id=\"basic\" realm=\"defaultRealm\">\n    18→    <user name=\"admin\" password=\"adminpwd\"/>\n    19→  </basicRegistry>\n    20→  <!-- JDBC config -->\n    21→  <library id=\"jdbcLib\">\n    22→    <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib/global/\" includes=\"*.jar\"/>\n    23→  </library>\n    24→\n    25→  <dataSource id=\"ordersDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/ordersDS\">\n    26→    <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"jdbcLib\"/>\n    27→    <properties databaseName=\"${env.DB_NAME}\" user=\"${env.DB_USER}\" password=\"${env.DB_PASS}\" serverName=\"${env.DB_HOST}\" portNumber=\"${env.DB_PORT}\"/>\n    28→  </dataSource>\n    29→\n    30→</server>\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86bc93ea-d546-4f4a-b95a-7e6c0d3fd59b","uuid":"08017d24-f574-4d36-b7a9-296f2a34a917"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UNiRE2wBRVDGJQUTQWyfK7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     2→<html lang=\"en\">\n     3→<head>\n     4→    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n     5→    <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n     6→    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n     7→    <meta name=\"format-detection\" content=\"telephone=no\">\n     8→    <!-- The above 3 meta tags *must* come first in the head; any other head content must come *after* these tags -->\n     9→    <title>Quarkus Coffee Shop</title>\n    10→    <link rel=\"apple-touch-icon\" sizes=\"180x180\" href=\"favicon/apple-touch-icon.png\">\n    11→    <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/png\" sizes=\"32x32\" href=\"favicon/favicon-32x32.png\">\n    12→    <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/png\" sizes=\"16x16\" href=\"favicon/favicon-16x16.png\">\n    13→    <link rel=\"manifest\" href=\"favicon/site.webmanifest\">\n    14→    <link rel=\"mask-icon\" href=\"favicon/safari-pinned-tab.svg\" color=\"#5bbad5\">\n    15→    <link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"favicon/favicon.ico\">\n    16→    <meta name=\"msapplication-TileColor\" content=\"#da532c\">\n    17→    <meta name=\"msapplication-config\" content=\"favicon/browserconfig.xml\">\n    18→    <meta name=\"theme-color\" content=\"#ffffff\">\n    19→    <!-- Bootstrap -->\n    20→    <link href=\"vendor/bootstrap/5.3.3/css/bootstrap.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    21→    <!-- Base Styles -->\n    22→    <link href=\"css/styles.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    23→    <!-- Custom CSS -->\n    24→    <link href=\"css/custom.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    25→    <!-- Google Fonts -->\n    26→    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Cookie%7cMontserrat:300,400,500,600,700%7cRoboto:300,400,500,700\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    27→    <!-- Font Awesome -->\n    28→    <link href=\"https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" integrity=\"sha384-wvfXpqpZZVQGK6TAh5PVlGOfQNHSoD2xbE+QkPxCAFlNEevoEH3Sl0sibVcOQVnN\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\">\n    29→    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/animate.css/3.5.2/animate.min.css\">\n    30→    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/ekko-lightbox/5.3.0/ekko-lightbox.css\">\n    31→    <!-- Customized css -->\n    32→    <link href=\"css/cafe.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" />\n    33→    <link href=\"css/toastr.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    34→    <!-- HTML5 shim and Respond.js for IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->\n    35→    <!-- WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file:// -->\n    36→    <!--[if lt IE 9]>\n    37→    <script src=\"https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.3/html5shiv.min.js\"></script>\n    38→    <script src=\"https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js\"></script>\n    39→    <![endif]-->\n    40→</head>\n    41→<body>\n    42→<nav class=\"navbar navbar-inverse navbar-fixed-top\">\n    43→    <div class=\"container\">\n    44→        <!-- Brand and toggle get grouped for better mobile display -->\n    45→        <div class=\"navbar-header\">\n    46→            <button type=\"button\" class=\"navbar-toggler collapsed\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#bs-example-navbar-collapse-1\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n    47→                <span class=\"sr-only\">Toggle navigation</span>\n    48→                <span class=\"icon-bar\"></span>\n    49→                <span class=\"icon-bar\"></span>\n    50→                <span class=\"icon-bar\"></span>\n    51→            </button>\n    52→            <a class=\"navbar-brand active\" href=\"#banner\"><i class=\"fa fa-coffee\"></i> Quarkus Coffee Shop</a>\n    53→        </div>\n    54→        <!-- Collect the nav links, forms, and other content for toggling -->\n    55→        <div class=\"collapse navbar-collapse\" id=\"bs-example-navbar-collapse-1\">\n    56→            <ul class=\"nav navbar-nav navbar-right\">\n    57→                <li><a href=\"#about\">About</a></li>\n    58→                <li><a href=\"#menu\">Menu</a></li>\n    59→                <li><a href=\"#gallery\">Gallery</a></li>\n    60→                <li><a href=\"#team\">Team</a></li>\n    61→                <li><a href=\"#testimonials\">Twitter</a></li>\n    62→                <li><a href=\"#contact\">Contact</a></li>\n    63→                <li id=\"rewards_link\" class=\"nav-item\"><a class=\"nav-link\" data-bs-toggle=\"modal\" data-bs-target=\"#rewardsModal\">Rewards</a></li>\n    64→            </ul>\n    65→        </div>\n    66→        <!-- /.navbar-collapse -->\n    67→    </div>\n    68→    <!-- /.container -->\n    69→</nav>\n    70→<span id=\"banner\"></span>\n    71→<section class=\"banner\">\n    72→    <div class=\"jumbotron\">\n    73→        <div class=\"container\">\n    74→            <div class=\"content\">\n    75→                <h5>Established 2020</h5>\n    76→                <h1>Quarkus Coffee Shop</h1>\n    77→                <a href=\"#menu\" class=\"btn\">Place an Order</a>\n    78→            </div>\n    79→        </div>\n    80→    </div>\n    81→</section>\n    82→\n    83→<div class=\"modal\" id=\"rewardsModal\">\n    84→    <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n    85→        <form id=\"rewards_modal\">\n    86→\n    87→            <div class=\"modal-content\">\n    88→                <!-- Modal Header -->\n    89→                <div class=\"modal-header\">\n    90→                    <h4 class=\"modal-title\">\n    91→                        Rewards Info\n    92→                    </h4>\n    93→                    <button id=\"btn_cancel\" type=\"button\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" aria-label=\"Close\"></button>\n    94→                </div>\n    95→                <!-- Modal body -->\n    96→                <div class=\"modal-body flex-fill d-inline-flex\">\n    97→                    <div class=\"flex-fill d-inline-flex justify-content-end form-group\">\n    98→                        <label for=\"rewards_id\" class=\"mr-sm-2 input-cafe text-nowrap mb-2\">Rewards email:</label>\n    99→                        <input type=\"email\" required class=\"form-control mb-2 mr-sm-2\" placeholder=\"Enter rewards email\" id=\"rewards_id\" rewards_id=\"rewards_id\">\n   100→                    </div>\n   101→                </div>\n   102→\n   103→                <!-- Modal footer -->\n   104→                <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n   105→                    <div class=\"flex-fill\">\n   106→                        <button type=\"submit\" id=\"rewards_entered\" class=\"btn-sm btn-primary pull-right\">Done</button>\n   107→                    </div>\n   108→                </div>\n   109→            </div>\n   110→        </form>\n   111→    </div>\n   112→</div>\n   113→\n   114→<span class=\"anchor\" id=\"about\"></span>\n   115→<section class=\"about\">\n   116→    <div class=\"container padding-2x\">\n   117→        <div class=\"row text-wrap\">\n   118→            <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n   119→                <h3 class=\"text-center\">Welcome to Quarkus, Kafka, Kubernetes, and Coffee</h3>\n   120→                <hr>\n   121→                <p class=\"text-center\">Quarkus is a Kubernetes Native Java stack tailored for OpenJDK HotSpot and GraalVM, crafted from the best of breed Java libraries and standards.</p>\n   122→            </div>\n   123→        </div>\n   124→        <div class=\"row about-info\">\n   125→            <div class=\"col-sm-12 col-md-6\">\n   126→                <div class=\"box wow fadeIn\" data-wow-duration=\"400ms\" data-wow-offset=\"10\">\n   127→                    <img src=\"images/about.jpg\" alt=\"about\" />\n   128→                </div>\n   129→            </div>\n   130→            <div class=\"col-sm-12 col-md-6\">\n   131→                <div class=\"box wow fadeIn\" data-wow-duration=\"800ms\" data-wow-offset=\"10\">\n   132→                    <h5>Our Story</h5>\n   133→                    <p>A Kubernetes Native Java stack tailored for OpenJDK HotSpot and GraalVM, crafted from the best of breed Java libraries and standards.</p>\n   134→                    <p>Quarkus tailors your application for GraalVM and HotSpot. Amazingly fast boot time, incredibly low RSS memory (not just heap size!) offering near instant scale up and high density memory utilization in container orchestration platforms like Kubernetes.</p>\n   135→                    <p>This application is demo showcasing an event driven Quarkus application that uses Apache Kafka for messaging.</p>\n   136→                </div>\n   137→            </div>\n   138→        </div>\n   139→    </div>\n   140→</section>\n   141→<span class=\"anchor\" id=\"menu\"></span>\n   142→<section class=\"menu\">\n   143→    <div class=\"container padding-2x\">\n   144→        <div class=\"row text-wrap\">\n   145→            <div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n   146→                <h3 class=\"text-center\">Menu</h3>\n   147→                <hr>\n   148→                <p class=\"text-center\">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Integer nec odio. Praesent libero. Sed cursus ante dapibus diam. Sed nisi. </p>\n   149→            </div>\n   150→        </div>\n   151→        <div class=\"modal\" id=\"myModal\">\n   152→            <div class=\"modal-dialog\" display=\"flex\">\n   153→                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n   154→                    <!-- Modal Header -->\n   155→                    <div class=\"modal-header\">\n   156→                        <h4 class=\"modal-title\" >\n   157→                            Current Order\n   158→                        </h4>\n   159→                        <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" aria-label=\"Close\"></button>\n   160→                        <div class=\"pt-10\">\n   161→                           